			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">(This is an updated repost of a guide that I did in the earlier days of LDoN, for some reason it was moved to the Quest and Equipment Forum of all things, and was practically unfindable via the search function.  The original post has been edited out - and the current version of the guide will be here as the Spells forum makes a WEE bit more sense ;)   )
<br />

<br />
As most of the chest cracking info out there seems scattered, fragmentary, and sometimes just plain whacked I present to you.. 
<br />

<br />
WUGGANS FOR FUN AND PROFIT: 
<br />

<br />
(This guide would serve for the priestly type container spells just as well - merely substitue the names of the appropriate spells/class where necessary. H.) 
<br />

<br />
Ok - I've opened a lot of these damn things - I call it learning through being blown up till ya learn - catchy eh? Herein lies a summary of what's up with chests, chest spells, locks, and alien corn embargoes. Ok - embargoes maybe not. 
<br />

<br />
Step 1: Hey look a chest/box/turnip! If you have a cleric/healer with lots of mana and remove curse spells, you can stop to play with it. Otherwise I seriously suggest waiting until you have already reached your adventure goal, and coming back to it. 
<br />

<br />
Step 2: Do not inspect the damn coffin/barrel/rabid monkey whatever. Don't. It's fairly liable to set it off. The inspect message also often lies like a rug. This is what Wuggan's Xxxxxx Appraisal is for. This line of spells (along with all other trap lines) is available at any Wayfarer camp adventure merchant, and can be purchased at any of these locations with points from any dungeon. 
<br />
Yes, this spell can occaisonally set it off - but it's less likely than /inspecting to do so in my experience. It uses a detect traps skill at approximately bard cap levels.  Wizards are better at this - they have rogue skill cap level detects.  If they're there and they have it, let them do it.  
<br />
Get RIGHT UP next to the chest, target it, and cast appraisal - you have to be VERY near to see the message the spell generates. Assuming you didn't blow up... 
<br />

<br />
Step 3: You get a message back from the Appraisal spell. This can be one of 4 things. 
<br />

<br />
A. You cannot determine if a whatsis is trapped. One of 2 things here, you may have simply failed to figure it out. Suggest casting this spell at least 3 times when getting this message to see if you get another sort. OR it means that this chest is mechanically trapped/locked - you can't do anything useful with it. Walk away. If there's a bard or rogue there it's their business. You are now done with this chest yourself. I repeat - you cannot open this chest safely. IF your healer has lot of mana and remove curse, and there is no rogue/bard available - hit it with a melee attack ONCE.  ONCE.  If a trap goes off you cannot open this chest without destroying the contents - move on.  If a trap does not go off, go ahead and have people attack and break it and loot up.
<br />

<br />
B. You are certain a thingamajig is trapped. Lucky you - this is a magically trapped/locked chest. You can work with it. On to Step 4. 
<br />

<br />
C. You are certain a higgedy is not trapped. BALONEY. It is too. They're all trapped. Lies lies lies. Well maybe not. Cast Appraisal again a time or 2 to make sure - if you get a different message of course act accordlingly. 
<br />

<br />
D. A container has resisted your Xxxxxx spell. NOTE: You cannot debuff a chest in any way shape or form - don't waste your time - it doesn't work. 
<br />
This object is cursed - only a priest can handle making it safe to play with. Don't waste any more time on it yourself - it's the healer's job. You cannot I will say again cannot open this chest safely yourself.  Once again you CAN try the hit once method to see if it's trapped or not if the healer has enough mana to deal with the potential consqequences.  If it's not trapped bash it on open, if it is walk away.
<br />

<br />
These are the only 4 messages you'll be getting - the proper reactions are as outlined above. 
<br />

<br />
Step 4. Time to get this damn thing de-dangerified. Load up Wuggan's Xxxxxx Discombobulation. Stand where ya did for the appraise and cast it. Once again 4 messages are possible. 
<br />

<br />
A. You have disarmed a whatever. Good for you - on to step 5 - it is no longer trapped. You will lose one Xxxxx Scrying Crystal from your inventory for this successful disarmament. These stackable components are available from the Magus Xxxxxx individuals at any Wayfarer camp, right click them and scroll down a bit - Greaters cost me about 17pp at 98 Charisma. Lesser spells use lesser crystals, etc etc. 
<br />

<br />
B. You have failed to disarm a widget. Ok - this isn't hard either. It didn't work. However, you still lose a scrying crystal from your stash - grumble snort oh well. Try again till you get the first message about it being disarmed successfully. Or ya blow up.  Or ya run out of crystals.
<br />

<br />
C. Paraphrase : You are not certain if a thingamagummy is trapped yet. You get this one if you haven't cast Appraisal yet. Cast Appraisal ya lazy. You also get this if you Appraise, zone out and come back without having disarmed. If you do that you need to Appraise again. 
<br />

<br />
D. Resist message again. Same procedure as Appraisal Resists. Why are you casting disarm on a cursed chest ya dingdong? 
<br />

<br />
If you haven't gotten the message about it being disarmed yet you'd better not be going to step 5 ;p 
<br />

<br />
Step 5: Yay the chest is now safe! Let's open it. Err what's this lock thing? Yes it's now time for Wuggan's Xxxxxxx Extrication. Stand where ya did to cast the first 2 spells, and cast this one onto your targeted item. Only 3 results here. 
<br />

<br />
A. You have failed to pick a whateverthehellitis. Rocket science, no! You blew it. But since the trap's gone no harm no foul - just keep casting it. 
<br />

<br />
B. You have picked a randomweirdcontainer. Good for you - it's now unlocked. Proceed to step 6. Excellent work. 
<br />

<br />
C. Resist Message yet again. Same as Appraisal Resist message procedure. Would you quit messing with the cursed chest ya dork? 
<br />

<br />
Step 6: Target your container and type /open. It will open up. You now right click to loot it. But wait - 9/10 times you can't loot this object yet - you get a dumb message saying so. This is a common and continuous bug in LDoN. BUT - you don't usually need to log and come back. Almost invariably SOMEONE in your party can loot the item. So just have everyone try.  
<br />
If no one can and you have a feign death class with you, have them flop successfully and loot. 
<br />
f that doesn't work you can try CoHing someone a ways away from the chest and see if they can get into it.
<br />
If none of that works well - log, come back, loot.
<br />

<br />
Grats -you have successfully dealt with the evil container of doom and fluffy kittens - you is uber. 
<br />

<br />
(Thanks to many tower posters for help with verifying data / telling me things I didn't know or had forgotten to add   :)
<br />

<br />
Here ends our guide - enjoy. 
<br />

<br />
Hraefn Nevermore</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Hraefn on Mon Jul 19, 2004 6:24 pm; edited 7 times in total</span></td>
