				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sorry - due to major r/l issues I can't play atm and am thus not reading these all that often.  
<br />

<br />
To answer the question - yes, "covered in a soft glow" usually means you were too far away to see the actual lock/trap message.  "covered..." is just the generic spell message and you'll see that from farther out than the actual useful result messages.
<br />

<br />
I've also gotten that VERY occaisonally standing practically on top of the chest.  If that's the case suggest moving to a new location but still very near the chest and cast again.  Sometimes you get stupid Z access issues, or it just plain gets bugged for a cast or 2.
<br />

<br />
Hope it's of some use.
<br />

<br />
H.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
