			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1.  Many times, a lot of people don't bother with chests or even think much about them.  But likely they are either not the appropriate class, or just haven't invested in the spells (they're dirt cheap, actually, especially compared to Pet Rune 3).
<br />

<br />
2.  Soft LDONs do not seem to have as nice of a payout as Hard LDONs.  At ~17pp per cast of Wuggan's Greater Discombobulation, in a soft LDON I'm going to flat-out assert ownership of the loot.  If it's rollable loot, it doesn't hurt to ask for the value of the stones out of the presplit, since clerics are entitled to the same for spending a fortune on peridots buffing your puny behind.  This probably also depends on server, group, ML liberties, and other assumptions, so weight the value of this note against your situation.
<br />

<br />
3.  Discombobulation resists actually do consume your scrying stone.  I've lost several on a single chest before it was disarmed.  And the loot was 10g, and a 1 charge illusion gnome potion.  Nodrop.  Wait, I am a gnome!
<br />

<br />
4.  People are idiots.  Don't let any melee type anywhere near the chest.  They tend to get physical with it and set it off.  Try everything you possibly can (rogues, clerics, appraising again ...) before you let them touch it as an absolute last resort.
<br />

<br />
5.  XP.  It's the equivalent of killing one mob.  Wait until the LDON is done, everyone has left, *then* loot.  All the XP is then yours.  Not really worth that much since you can kill extra mobs faster than solving the chest.
<br />

<br />
What they really need to do is give adventure points for chests.  51 just isn't enough, it'll take a while before I get a full set of MMC armor.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
